data.title: EIGHT DAYS OF SUMMER
data.meta_description: Sixty-three years ago, Keith Campbell won the 350 Dutch TT at Assen and the Belgian Grand Prix at Spa-Francorchamps, iconic circuits that required riding precision. He became the first Australian to claim two world championship GPs in a calendar year, and captured the lead in a title race he would eventually win. The Assen victory [â€¦]
